            <thetext>In one of my libraries, my editor auto-insert a newline to wrap the &quot;description&quot; string in the Manifest file, which meant there was a description string which did not terminate with a trailing quote before the end of line. The output produced by &quot;generate.py source&quot; for the application did not provide any indication of where the error was:

----------------------------------------------------------------------------
    Initializing: rte
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
&gt;&gt;&gt; Processing configuration
Invalid control character &#39;\n&#39; at: line 8 column 1 (char 202)


Even with -v, there is no indication of what file this error occurred in.

The error should include the name of the file in which the error was encountered.</thetext>
